  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 5 March 1925
---
He cannot cease to be because hideous immoralities or inhuman brutalities
are committed in His name. He is long-suffering. He is patient but He is
also terrible. He is the most exacting personage in "the world and the
world to come. He metes out the same measure to us that we mete out to our
neighbours -- men and brutes. With Him ignorance is no excuse. And withal
He is ever forgiving for He always gives us the chance to repent.
